(40, '2015-06-07 21:59:09', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35007, 'unchanged', 'Beaches-East York', 'Ontario', 'Strong NDP Incumbent', 'Although many Liberals have high hopes of regaining Beaches-East York from the NDP because the Liberals took the riding provincially in 2014, none of the same circumstances prevail.  The Provincial NDP MPP, Michael Prue, was narrowly defeated by the Liberals due to a strong mandate for Kathleen Wynne across the province and a a reluctance among NDP voters to endorse a provincial NDP campaign that went against their beliefs and interests.  The federal situation is very different.  NDP incumbent Matthew Kellway  has served the riding well, focusing on Urban Affairs, something missing from the Conservative policies.  The policies of the Federal NDP are better aligned with local values than those of the provincial wing.  Kellway''s most energetic challenger is a young lawyer, Nathaniel Erskine-Smith, running for the Liberals.  He is new to politics, insecure, and leans heavily on the local machines that got the very blue Liberal elected provincially.  The Liberals would be better off contesting winnable ridings in other parts of Toronto. Bill Burrows is running for the Conservatives', '', '', '', 11067, 14967, 20265, 2240, 0, 130, -3900, -9198, 48669, 37472, 77, 'NDP', 9198, 48669, 18.8991),
(41, '2015-06-08 16:02:54', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35008, 'new', 'Brampton Centre', 'Ontario', 'Getting out the vote is key to taking this riding from the Conservatives', 'This is a riding where getting out the vote is extremely important.  Last election voters in the new riding of Brampton Centre, who were voting in Brampton-Springdale or Bramalea-Gore-Malton, came out in extremely low numbers.  Redistribution has taken strong Liberal opposition from Brampton-Springdale and strong NDP opposition from Bramalea-Gore-Malton and put them into a riding where previous voting patterns predict a split opposition and a likely Conservative win.  It will take a combination of getting more voters out and lining up behind one candidate to take this riding from the Conservatives.  Rameshwer Sangha is running for the Liberals, Rosemary Keenan for the NDP.  Conservative incumbent Bal Gosal is running for re-election.', '', '', '', 16148, 8822, 8074, 1548, 0, 205, 7326, 8074, 34797, 18444, 53, 'Tory', 7326, 34797, 21.0535),
(42, '2015-06-02 20:04:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35009, 'redistricted', 'Brampton East', 'Ontario', '', 'Brampton East is a new riding composed primarily of the northern half of the old riding of Bramalea-Gore-Malton.  This part of the riding has traditionally voted NDP; however, the addition of a more Conservative section from Brampton-Springdale will make this a three-way race.  Raj Grewal is running for the Liberals; none of the other parties have yet chosen their candidates.', '', '', '', 8439, 8774, 10775, 487, 0, 147, -335, -2336, 28622, 20036, 70, 'NDP', 2336, 28622, 8.16155),
