(60, '2015-06-02 20:06:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35027, 'redistricted', 'Etobicoke Centre', 'Ontario', 'This may be a very tight race.', 'Etobicoke Centre has almost the same boundaries as it did in the previous election.  Last election it was the closest riding in the country, taken by the Conservatives by 9 votes, after recounts.  The changes in boundaries, which may appear minor, would favour the Conservatives if voting patterns from the last election were to remain the same.  A small area between Martin Grove, Eglinton and the 401 that came in strongly for the Liberals last time has been switched over to Etobicoke North, replaced by a small area south of Burnamthorpe that leaned Conservative.  Although these changes would mean that the margin of victory would not be razor thin, it is still expected to be an extremely close race between the Liberals, represented by Borys Wrzesnewsky, and incumbent Conservative Ted Opitz.', '', '', '', 22306, 21616, 7792, 1431, 0, 146, 690, 14514, 53291, 30839, 58, 'Tory', 690, 53291, 1.29478),
(61, '2015-06-02 20:06:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35028, 'redistricted', 'Etobicoke-Lakeshore', 'Ontario', 'Too close to call.', 'This is a riding that should be ripe for the Liberals to take back; the Conservative win in 2011 could be attributed to the fact that Michael Ignatieff, whose popularity as Liberal leader was very low, was running.  Etobicoke Lakeshore, which has very similar boundaries to its previous incarnation, has switched back to voting Liberal provincially and seemed to be fertile ground for a local Liberal to take back.  The abrupt departure of Susan Watts as candidate leaves us scratching our heads.  No forecasting will be possible until another candidate is chosen.', '', '', '', 20484, 17867, 10336, 2046, 0, 182, 2617, 10148, 50915, 30249, 59, 'Tory', 2617, 50915, 5.13994),
(62, '2015-06-04 18:56:17', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35029, 'redistricted', 'Etobicoke North', 'Ontario', 'Strong Liberal Incumbent', 'Kirsty Duncan, the Liberal Incumbent for this riding, has been a strong spokesperson on behalf of International Development and Women''s rights.  She is running for re-election, challenged by Faisal Hassan for the NDP and Akhtar Ayub for the Green Party.  The Conservatives have not yet announced their candidate.', '', '', '', 11208, 14929, 8283, 59, 0, 594, -3721, 2925, 35073, 23271, 66, 'Lib', 3721, 35073, 10.6093),
