(64, '2015-06-08 01:43:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35031, 'redistricted', 'Glengarry-Prescott-Russell', 'Ontario', 'Strategic voting needed', 'Glengarry-Prescott-Russell looks like a riding that could change hands with some effort.  It would take a few Conservatives to become disillusioned with the Harper Government, as well as the non-Conservative voters getting behind one candidate who could win the riding.  The Conservative incumbent is Pierre Lemieux.  Francis Drouin is running for the Liberals and Normand Laurin for the NDP.', '', '', '', 26802, 16801, 9149, 1966, 0, 187, 10001, 17653, 54905, 27916, 51, 'Tory', 10001, 54905, 18.2151),
