(92, '2015-06-07 21:38:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35059, 'redistricted', 'Mississauga East–Cooksville', 'Ontario', 'Increased voter turnout key to defeating the Conservative', 'In 2011 voters in this riding elected Conservative incumbent Wladyslaw Lizon, best noted for sending constituents in this diverse riding a questionnaire asking <a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/politics/ottawa-notebook/tory-mp-to-his-south-asian-constituents-do-you-speak-indian/article2309781/"> whether their native language is "Indian."</a>  Voter turnout in 2011 was very low, so getting out the non-Conservative vote is key to taking back this riding.  Peter Fonseca, the former Liberall MPP for this riding is running this time, along with Ali Naqvi for the NDP.', '', '', '', 19269, 15999, 7814, 959, 0, 209, 3270, 11455, 44250, 24772, 56, 'Tory', 3270, 44250, 7.38983),
(93, '2015-06-02 21:10:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35060, 'redistricted', 'Mississauga-Erin Mills', 'Ontario', 'Worth voting strategically to defeat the Conservative.', 'Mississauga-Erin Mills is composed of most of the old riding of Mississauga-Erindale.  Although the majority of voters in Mississauga-Erindale did not vote Conservative, incumbent Bob Dechert won with a fairly comfortable margin.  Since some scandals have made him vulnerable it is worth trying to get behind one of the opposing parties.  Traditionally the Liberals have been a strong second; this time Iqra Khalid will run for the Liberal party, Michelle Bilek will run for the NDP and Andrew Roblin for the Green Party.\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', 21646, 15978, 7503, 1274, 0, 66, 5667, 14143, 46468, 24756, 53, 'Tory', 5667, 46468, 12.1955),
(94, '2015-06-02 21:04:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35061, 'redistricted', 'Mississauga-Lakeshore', 'Ontario', 'Worth voting strategically to try to defeat the Conservative.', 'This is a new riding composed of most of the old riding of Mississauga South.  It is currently held by Conservative Stella Ambler, who is running for re-election, but expect a strong challenge from Liberal Sven Spengemann, who worked on the United Nations Assistance Mission for Iraq.  Eric Guerbilsky is running for the NDP.', '', '', '', 24269, 19068, 6616, 1592, 0, 195, 5201, 17653, 51740, 27276, 53, 'Tory', 5201, 51740, 10.0522),
(95, '2015-06-02 21:09:25', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35062, 'redistricted', 'Mississauga-Malton', 'Ontario', 'This riding could be a battleground.', 'This is a new riding composed of much of the old riding of Mississauga-Brampton South, where the Conservatives took the riding last time, but includes a large stretch north of Pearson Airport, which has traditionally voted Liberal and NDP.  Based on previous election results, this may be one of the most closely fought ridings in the country, with a battle between the Liberals and Conservatives.  Navdeep Bains is running for the Liberals, Jagdish Grewal for the Conservatives.  Last election this riding also had one of the lowest rates of voter turnout in the country, so a strong effort to get out the non-Conservative vote could change the riding.', '', '', '', 13715, 13477, 8584, 744, 0, 113, 238, 5131, 36633, 22805, 62, 'Tory', 238, 36633, 0.649687),
(96, '2015-06-02 21:09:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35063, 'redistricted', 'Mississauga-Streetsville', 'Ontario', 'Worth voting strategically to try to defeat the Conservative.', 'Most voters in Mississauga-Streetsville will be voting in the same riding, with the addition on some new voters in the northern part east of Erin Mills.   Although the riding is currently held by Conservative Brad Butt, expect a strong challenge by Liberal Gagan Sikand.', '', '', '', 21324, 16179, 7033, 1691, 0, 10, 5145, 14291, 46237, 24903, 54, 'Tory', 5145, 46237, 11.1275),
