(126, '2015-06-03 20:54:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35093, 'redistricted', 'Scarborough-Agincourt', 'Ontario', 'This riding is the Liberals to lose.', 'The graph on this page shows the results of the by-election of 2014, when the riding gave the Liberals, represented by Arnold Chan, a much wider victory than they had for his predecessor Jim Karygiannis in the 2011 General election. Chan is running for re-election, challenged by Bin Chang for the Conservatives.  So far the other parties have not nominated candidates. ', '', '', '', 6344, 12868, 1838, 307, 0, 315, -4310, 6099, 37738, 24851, 66, 'Lib', 4310, 37738, 11.4208),
(127, '2015-06-02 21:25:24', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35094, 'redistricted', 'Scarborough Centre', 'Ontario', 'A close three-way race is possible.', 'Last election this was a three-way race narrowly won by Conservative Roxanne James.   She is running for re-election against Liberal challenger Salmer Zahid and Alex Wilson for the NDP, who will both battle hard for the riding.  Historically the riding has voted for all three parties.  Non-Conservative voters will need to keep their ears to the ground to decide whether to vote Liberal or NDP to ensure a Conservative defeat - national trends of one party rising in popularity are not always reflected in the riding.  Last election the voter turnout was below the national average, so getting out the non-Conservative vote will be key in what may be a close race.\r\n', '', '', '', 12841, 11738, 11285, 946, 0, 0, 1103, 1556, 36810, 23969, 65, 'Tory', 1103, 36810, 2.99647),
(128, '2015-06-02 21:25:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35095, 'redistricted', 'Scarborough-Guildwood', 'Ontario', 'A riding that needs to be held', 'Scarborough-Guildwood is slightly smaller now, as parts of it have been redistributed to other ridings.  The riding is held by Liberal John McKay, who is running for re-election, but based on voting patterns from previous elections, expect a close race between McKay and Conservative Kazimierz Konkel.   In previous elections the voter turnout in this riding has been well below the average for Canada.', '', '', '', 11999, 12380, 9237, 769, 0, 206, -381, 2762, 34591, 22386, 65, 'Lib', 381, 34591, 1.10144),
