(131, '2015-06-07 19:51:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35098, 'redistricted', 'Scarborough Southwest', 'Ontario', '', 'Most voters in Scarborough Southwest, held by NDP Dan Harris, are in the same riding as in 2011, with the exception of a few north of Eglinton and some east of Bellamy.  Last time the riding was a three-way race with a voter turnout that was lower than average.  NDP incumbent Dan Harris is running for re-election against challengers that have not yet been nominated.  Bill Blair is a high-profile candidate seeking the Liberal nomination.', '', '', '', 12474, 11554, 13731, 1600, 0, 20, 920, -1257, 38753, 26259, 68, 'NDP', 1257, 38753, 3.24362),
