(141, '2015-06-03 19:34:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35108, 'redistricted', 'Toronto Centre', 'Ontario', 'A Liberal-NDP contest', 'Toronto Centre covers a smaller geographical area now, since the northern part was carved off to join the new riding of University-Rosedale, and a slice was removed from the south to be part of Spadina-Fort York.  The riding now goes from the Bloor Viaduct to the Gardiner, from the Don Valley Parkway to Bay Street.  The chart on this page shows the results of the 2013 by-election, when Bob Rae stepped down and Chrystia Freeland became the new Liberal Member of Parliament, despite a strong showing for New Democrat Linda McQuaig.  McQuaig is running for the NDP again against Bill Morneau for the Conservatives, since the incumbent is running in the northern half of the riding, now University-Rosedale.  The Conservative and Green parties have not yet chosen their candidates. ', '', '', '', 3004, 17194, 12640, 1034, 0, 949, -8352, -7141, 37350, 30387, 81, 'Lib', 8352, 37350, 22.3614),
(142, '2015-06-07 22:04:48', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 35109, 'unchanged', 'Toronto Danforth', 'Ontario', 'A strong NDP incumbent', 'Toronto Danforth has been electing NDP representatives since 2004, when Jack Layton, newly elected leader of the NDP, won the riding from Liberal Dennis Mills.  Due to Layton''s tragic death in 2011 a by-election was held in 2012.  Craig Scott, lawyer and human rights advocate, ran for the NDP and was given a mandate as strong as Layton''s had been, as shown in the graphic on this page. Scott, who focuses on Democratic reform, is running for re-election this year, challenged by Tim Dutaud for the Conservatives and Chris Tolley for the Green Party; the Liberals have not yet chosen a candidate.', '', '', '', 1736, 9215, 19210, 1517, 0, 641, -13350, -1587, 39086, 31814, 81, 'NDP', 11059, 39086, 28.294),
