(183, '2015-06-04 13:59:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 48001, 'redistricted', 'Banff-Airdrie', 'Alberta', '', 'Banff-Airdrie is a new riding taken from the former riding of Wild Rose.  It still features some of the most breathtaking landscapes in Canada, but covers about half the territory.  Blake Richards, the mask-obsessed incumbent for Wild Rose, is running for re-election in this riding.  Marlo Raynolds is running for the Liberals.  Other parties have not yet announced their candidates.', '', '', '', 29938, 3411, 5534, 3277, 0, 165, 26527, 24604, 42125, 12022, 29, 'Tory', 24604, 42125, 58.4071),
(184, '2015-06-08 21:46:53', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 48002, 'redistricted', 'Battle River-Crowfoot', 'Alberta', '', 'Battle River-Crowfoot is a new riding made of a combination of Crowfoot and Vegreville--Wainwright, with a handful of voters from the ridings of Medicine Hat and Wetaskiwin.  These ridings have been electing Reform/Alliance members for many years now, and have continued to do so as the name changed to Conservative.  Kevin Sorenson, the MP for Crowfoot, will run for re-election in Battle-River-Crowfoot.  Only the Green Party has nominated a candidate so far: actor Gary Kelly.', '', '', '', 39645, 1028, 4694, 1859, 0, 487, 38626, 34960, 47722, 7581, 16, 'Tory', 34960, 47722, 73.2576),
