(186, '2015-06-03 18:08:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 48004, 'redistricted', 'Calgary Centre', 'Alberta', 'This is an open race.', 'The Conservatives managed to hold on to Calgary Centre in the 2012 by-election, but by a much narrower margin than they had in the 2011 general election,  beating the Liberals by only a thousand votes. The Liberals and the Green party gained a considerable percentage of the vote, showing that all parties have a chance of winning  this riding.   Conservative Joan Crockatt is running for re-election against Kent Hehr for the Liberals.  Although the NDP and the Green party have not yet chosen a candidate, they can no longer be discounted in Alberta elections.  Keep an eye on developments to decide which opponent is best suited to defeat the incumbent.', '', '', '', 10191, 9033, 1064, 7090, 0, 262, 15023, 16664, 41450, 18493, 45, 'Tory', 15023, 41450, 36.2437),
