(188, '2015-06-02 08:33:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 48006, 'redistricted', 'Calgary Forest Lawn', 'Alberta', 'Increased voter turnout is key in this riding', 'Voters in Calgary Forest Lawn, formerly Calgary East, have been re-relecting Deepak Obhrai since 1997 as a representative for the Reform, Alliance and Conservative parties.  Although the vast majority of votes cast have gone his way, a much greater majority of voters in this part of Calgary, about 40,000 of them, have stayed home on election day.  Voter turnout here has been extraordinarily low.  If the voter turnout here were more similar to the rest of the country, about 15,000 extra voters would turn up at the polls.  If most of them decided to vote for change, the Conservative landslides would melt away.  Cam Stewart is running for the Liberals.  The NDP will soon nominate a candidate, and voters must discern which of the two is best positioned to take over from the incumbent.', '', '', '', 19574, 5397, 4064, 1638, 0, 227, 14177, 15510, 30900, 11099, 36, 'Tory', 14177, 30900, 45.8803),
