(384, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'This is a riding where there is some hope of defeating the Conservative incumbent, Gail Shea, who as Minister of Fisheries and Oceans has overseen the <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2014/01/30/fisheries-libraries-science-gail-shea_n_4693445.html"> destruction of countless volumes of research</a> on fisheries and allowing our protection of our fish stocks to become <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2014/06/02/marine-protection-canada-dead-last_n_5430038.html"> one of the worst in the world.</a>  Robert Morrissey is running for the Liberals, Herb Dickieson for the NDP, both candidates with experience in the P.E.I. legislature.  If voters could coalesce behind one of them it would be possible for this seat to change hands.', 'Egmont', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '11003', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/11003/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(376, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'Bonavista-Burin-Trinity is a new riding made up of parts of the old ridings of Random--Burin--St. George''s, Bonavista--Gander--Grand Falls--Windsor and Avalon.  All those ridings voted Liberal in the last election.  Judy Foote, the incumbent in Random—Burin—St. George''s, is running for re-election in this new riding.  The other parties have not yet announced their candidates.', 'Bonavista-Burin-Trinity', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10002', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10002/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(377, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'Coast of Bays-Central-Notre Dame is a new riding made up of parts of Bonavista--Gander--Grand Falls--Windsor, Humber--St. Barbe--Baie Verte and Random--Burin--St. George''s.  All three ridings voted Liberal in the last election, and Scott Simms, the Liberal member for Bonavista—Gander—Grand Falls—Windsor is running for re-election.  No other candidates have been nominated yet.', 'Coast of Bays-Central-Notre Dame', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10003', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10003/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(378, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'The graphic on this page shows the results of the 2013 by-election, where Yvonne Jones scored a decisive win for the Liberals over Peter Penashue, who had been forced to resign his seat due to allegations of spending irregularities.  Yvonne Jones is running again against opponents that have not yet been announced.', 'Labrador', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10004', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10004/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(379, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'The new riding of Long Range Mountains is on the western coast of the province and takes up parts of the old ridings of Humber--St. Barbe--Baie Verte and Random--Burin--St. George.  Gudrid Hutchings is running for the Liberals.  The other parties have not yet announced their candidates.', 'Long Range Mountains', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10005', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10005/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(380, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'NDP incumbent Jack Harris is running for office again.  He has been a key member of the shadow cabinet and Mulcair has said that he would play a key role in an NDP government should he form one.  Nick Whalen is running for the Liberals and David Peters for the Green Party.  The Conservatives have not yet named a candidate.', 'St John''s East', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10006', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10006/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(381, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'In the speculation as to whether NDP incumbent Ryan Cleary, <a href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/newfoundland-labrador/russell-crowe-s-i-love-newfoundland-tweet-used-in-ryan-cleary-rant-1.2865513">loyal to Newfoundland above everything else,</a> will face a real challenge from Seamus O''Regan, another journalist running for the Liberals, it is hoped that the Conservatives will not use the distraction to sneak in a more attractive candidate.', 'St John''s South-Mount Pearl', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10007', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10007/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(382, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'Cardigan is one of a few dozen ridings in the country whose boundaries have not changed since the last election.  Liberal incumbent Lawrence MacAulay is running for re-election.  The other parties have not yet announced their candidates.', 'Cardigan', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '11001', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/11001/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(383, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'Charlottetown is one of the few ridings in Canada whose boundaries are unchanged.  Liberal incumbent Sean Casey, whose eloquent critiques of the government can be read in the <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/sean-casey/"> Huffington Post,</a> is running for re-election.  Joe Byrne is running for the NDP and Rebecca Viau for the Green Party.  The Conservatives have not yet selected a candidate.', 'Charlottetown', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '11002', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/11002/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(375, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', 'This riding has the same name but keeps only some of its previous character.  Avalon voted Liberal in 2011, but a large Liberal-leaning portion has been moved to Bonavista-Burin-Trinity, and a large NDP-leaning portion from St. John''s East has been added to the riding.  This gives the Conservatives a theoretical advantage in this riding, based on previous voting patterns.  However, much will depend on who the candidates will be.  Scott Andrews, who was elected as a Liberal but  sat as an independent for some of the term, has announced his retirement from politics.  Yvonne Jones, who won the by-election in Labrador when Peter Panashue was forced to step down, is running for the Liberals in Avalon this time.  The other parties have not yet announced their candidates.', 'Avalon', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10001', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:12', '2015-06-28 23:47:12', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/10001/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
