(429, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:13', '2015-06-28 23:47:13', 'The chart on this page shows the results of the 2012 by-election, where voters in Durham gave more than 50% of the vote to Erin O''Toole, a similar proportion to the vote received by Bev Oda before she stepped down due to scandals.  Durham''s borders have changed and the riding covers a smaller geographical area, but the voting patterns in the smaller riding are similar to those in the larger one.  O''Toole is running for re-election, challenged by Corrina Traill for the Liberals and Derek Spence for the NDP.  Voters will need to decide which of the two has the better chance of defeating the incumbent.', 'Durham', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '35023', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:13', '2015-06-28 23:47:13', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/35023/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(430, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:14', '2015-06-28 23:47:14', 'Finance Minister Joe Oliver won this riding by a somewhat narrow margin in 2011, amidst rumours of electoral fraud.  Prior to 2011 the riding voted Liberal.  Statistically this is a riding that the Liberals might be able to take back, but much may depend on their choice of candidate.  Eve Adams, who defected from the Conservatives and currently represents Mississauga-Brampton South, plans to run for the nomination.  However many high-profile Liberals from the area have come out in support of Marco Mendecino, who has been very active in Eglinton-Lawrence Liberal politics and seems to have earned their loyalty.', 'Eglinton-Lawrence', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '35024', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:14', '2015-06-28 23:47:14', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/35024/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
