(507, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:16', '2015-06-28 23:47:16', 'The results of the 2014 by-election in Trinty-Spadina seem much more relevant to Spadina-Fort York than the 2011 General election results for Trinity-Spadina.  Adam Vaughan, who had gained trust and popularity as City Councillor, ran for the Liberals after New Democrat Olivia Chow stepped down to run for the mayoralty of Toronto.  Vaughan probably would have won the election no matter which party he had run for, but he chose the Liberals, and will run for re-election this year in Spadina-Fort York, the southern part of the former riding of Trinity-Spadina.  No other parties have chosen their candidates yet.', 'Spadina-Fort York', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '35101', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:16', '2015-06-28 23:47:16', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/35101/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
