(570, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:17', '2015-06-28 23:47:17', 'This oddly shaped new riding is composed a large part of Edmonton East and the southeast corner of Edmonton-St. Albert.  In 2011 both of those ridings elected Conservatives by a considerable margin.  The voter turnout in this part of Edmonton was extremely low – half the voters stayed home.  If voters in Edmonton Griesbach showed up at the rate of the average riding, the extra 10,000 voters could easily change the outcome of the election if they unite behind one of the opposition candidates. No incumbent is running in this riding.  Janis Irwin is running for the NDP, Kerry Diotte for the Conservatives, Daniol Coles for the Liberals and Heather Workman for the Green Party.', 'Edmonton Griesbach', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '48015', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:17', '2015-06-28 23:47:17', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/48015/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
