(615, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:19', '2015-06-28 23:47:19', 'This riding has a varied tradition of elected parties, from Reform/Alliance to Liberal to NDP, and it may continue to change allegiances.  In the last election the Conservatives came very close to taking the riding, and it is important to ensure that the seat does not go Conservative if the contest is perceived to be NDP vs. Green Party.  NDP incumbent Randall Garrison, who has focused on human rights and gender equity, is running for re-election.  Shari Lukens is running for the Conservatives, David Merner for the Liberals and Frances Litman for the Green Party.', 'Esquimalt–Saanich–Sooke', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '59026', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:19', '2015-06-28 23:47:19', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/59026/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
(616, 0, '2015-06-28 19:47:19', '2015-06-28 23:47:19', 'Saanich-Gulf Islands has slightly smaller borders than it did, as some areas have been redistributed to Saanich-Juan de Fuca and Victoria.  It is widely assumed that incumbent Elizabeth May will keep her seat, given her national popularity as the no-nonsense voice of reason. Tim Kane is running for the Liberals; the other parties have not yet chosen their candidates.', 'Saanich-Gulf Islands', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '59027', '', '', '2015-06-28 19:47:19', '2015-06-28 23:47:19', '', 0, 'http://defeatharper.ca/wordpress/59027/', 0, 'riding', '', 0),
